This product includes data model artifacts (JSON Schemas and example
payloads) derived from the Battery Pass Data Model:

  https://github.com/batterypass/BatteryPassDataModel

The Battery Pass Data Model was created by the Battery Pass Consortium
(thebatterypass.eu) and is licensed under the Creative Commons
Attribution 4.0 International License (CC-BY-4.0):

  https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

The vendored schemas under ./schemas/ may contain fixes relative to the
upstream repository. All modifications are documented in
./schemas/PATCHES.md.

License note on the vendored TTL sources (./ttl/): the upstream project
standardized its license to CC-BY-4.0 in October 2025; the TTL file
headers carry "SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-4.0" accordingly. Some
Aspect-level samm:description literals inside those files still embed a
stale earlier boilerplate paragraph referring to CC BY-NC 4.0. We treat
the file headers, the SPDX identifiers and the upstream README (all
CC-BY-4.0) as authoritative, and strip the stale paragraph from our
generated artifacts (see ./schemas/PATCHES.md section 5).

This product bundles snapshots of open datasets for risk screening,
documented with source and license in ./data/SOURCES.md, including:

  - EU indicative list of Conflict-Affected and High-Risk Areas (CAHRA),
    https://www.cahraslist.net/
  - Responsible Minerals Initiative (RMI) public facility lists,
    https://www.responsiblemineralsinitiative.org/
